-- Tanzania Tea Packers Posts Wider Annual Loss as Costs Increase
-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 2012-05-04T11:36:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/tanzania-tea-packers-posts-wider-annual-loss-as-costs-increase.html
Tanzania Tea Packers Ltd. said its
annual loss widened as the cost of sales increased.  The loss totaled 493.3 million Tanzanian shillings
($312,000) in the 12 months through December, compared with 32.4
million shillings a year earlier, the company said in a
statement published in the Dar es Salaam-based Daily News
newspaper today. The cost of sales climbed 17 percent to 9.6
billion shillings as marketing and distribution expenses jumped
36 percent, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam via Nairobi at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 